result.execSummary:
The defendant Jermaine Turner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jermaine Turner is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jermaine Turner was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Repeater]. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jermaine  Turner in court with attorney Nicole M. Masnica.  Lesli S. Boese appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Prosecuting attorney moves to amend Count 3 to Disorderly Conduct contrary to section 13.102(c)(8)  of the Waukesha County Code of Ordinances.  Court approves amendment.    Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 3,  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 1 and 2 dismissed.

Court orders the following: 
- Fine totaling: $367.50 to be paid at rate of $25.00 per month commencing March 1, 2015; alternate 8 days Huber
- Defendant may also perform alternate of 40 hours community service in lieu of payment of costs or fines.  Court must receive notice of completion prior to due date.
